@startuml modbus_state
title Windmeters Modbus Interface — Modbus RTU Line Discipline (mb driver)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor #F5F7F7
  BorderColor #5B6B6A
  ArrowColor #14746F
}

[*] --> Unsynced : reset

Unsynced : discard everything until\nthe bus is quiet (FR-S19)
Unsynced --> Idle : t3.5 bus-idle observed

Idle : RX armed on PD6 (default remap),\nDE low = receiver enabled
Idle --> Receiving : byte received

Receiving : accumulate bytes into the\n256-byte ADU buffer (FR-MB24)
Receiving --> Receiving : next byte within t3.5
Receiving --> Idle : FE / ORE poisons the frame\n(silent discard, FR-MB24)
Receiving --> Evaluate : t3.5 inter-frame gap\n(frame end, FR-MB03)

Evaluate : check CRC-16 then address
Evaluate --> Idle : bad CRC (FR-MB02) /\nother address or broadcast (FR-MB05/06) /\nrunt — silent discard
Evaluate --> Responding : valid frame addressed to us

state Responding {
  [*] --> TxPhase : remap PD6→TX (partial remap 2),\nassert DE before first start bit (FR-MB04)
  TxPhase : dispatch FC03/04/06/16;\npolled TX of the response (or exception 01/02/03)
  TxPhase --> RxPhase : last stop bit sent (TC),\nde-assert DE within one char (FR-MB04)
  RxPhase : remap PD6→RX (default map),\nflush self-echo (FR-MB23)
  RxPhase --> [*]
}

Responding --> Idle : re-arm; latency ≤ 15/100 ms (FR-MB20/21)

note as MBN
  Polled, zero-ISR: mb_poll() advances this
  machine each loop pass; mb_send() runs the
  Responding sub-states synchronously.
  HDSEL abandoned — remap-switching RX/TX
  eliminates the first-byte-after-idle loss.
end note
@enduml
